TY  - JOUR
AU  - Schroth, Enrique
AU  - Szalay, Dezsö
T1  - Cash Breeds Success: The Role of Financing Constraints in Patent Races*
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfp020
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 14
IS  - 1
SP  - 73
EP  - 118
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This paper studies the impact of financing constraints in patent races. We develop a model of optimal contracting where firms finance their R&amp;D expenditures with an investor who cannot verify their effort. In equilibrium, firms are more likely to win the more cash and assets they hold prior to the race, and the less cash and assets their rivals hold prior to the race. Evidence from US pharmaceutical patents awarded between 1975 and 1999 supports our theoretical predictions.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfp020
ER  - 



